HEADWORD: Eyelid
<hw>Eye`lid"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>The cover of the eye; that portion of movable skin with which an
animal covers or uncovers the eyeball at pleasure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>eye-lotion</ent>⟦br⟧
